[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi all,</p>\n<p>My typical workflow to get a working <code>.config</code>, that will compile rust, is as follows:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>check if rust toolchain is correct: <code>make rustavailable</code></li>\n<li><code>make tinyconfig &amp;&amp; make menuconfig</code></li>\n<li>In menu config, turn on 64 bit kernel and then rust support </li>\n<li><code>make LLVM=1</code></li>\n<li>Indiscriminately smash the enter key to make all of the questions about unset options go away :o)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Step 5 is probably to blame for this, but it did work for a while. Now I get this error (on <code>rust-next</code>):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">scripts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">generate_rust_target</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cmd</span>:<span class=\"mi\">1</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">missing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">separator</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">Stop</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">usr</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">local</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">google</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">mattgilbride</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span>:<span class=\"mi\">1179</span>: <span class=\"nc\">scripts</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span>:<span class=\"mi\">240</span>: <span class=\"nc\">__sub</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>So...two questions:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>What are the steps to get a minimally working <code>.config</code> that will compile rust? (<span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span>, you've mentioned the pitfalls of providing an \"easy button\" for this, but perhaps we should document it somewhere with a strong disclaimer?)</li>\n<li>What went wrong? Perhaps an opportunity for a better error message?</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Cheers, I'm happy to make some newbie contributions accordingly,</p>\n<p>Matt</p>",
        "id": 419016396,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1706699204
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For 5) you can <code>make olddefconfig</code></p>",
        "id": 419017980,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1706699843
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For the minimal config I have arrived at this: <code>make allnoconfig</code> and then merge in these:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>CONFIG_64BIT=y\nCONFIG_X86_64=y\nCONFIG_X86=y\n\nCONFIG_CC_OPTIMIZE_FOR_PERFORMANCE=y\nCONFIG_SMP=y\nCONFIG_KERNEL_XZ=y\nCONFIG_SLUB=y\nCONFIG_SLUB_TINY=y\n\nCONFIG_BINFMT_ELF=y\nCONFIG_BINFMT_SCRIPT=y\n\nCONFIG_MODULES=y\nCONFIG_MODULE_UNLOAD=y\n\nCONFIG_MODVERSIONS=n\nCONFIG_RUST=y\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 419019389,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1706700397
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>hm...<br>\n<code>make olddefconfig</code></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code>#\n#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">No</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">change</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span>\n#\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then, later, here is the first thing I'm blindly ignoring by accepting the default:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Link</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Time</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Optimization</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LTO</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">1.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">None</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LTO_NONE</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">2.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Clang</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Full</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LTO</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EXPERIMENTAL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LTO_CLANG_FULL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">NEW</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">3.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Clang</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ThinLTO</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EXPERIMENTAL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LTO_CLANG_THIN</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">NEW</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">choice</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>:\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I'm on a linux machine, x86_64, FWIW:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Operating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">System</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Debian</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GNU</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Linux</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rodete</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Kernel</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Linux</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">6.5.13</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"n\">rodete2</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">amd64</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Architecture</span>: <span class=\"nc\">x86</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">64</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 419019459,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1706700425
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For booting in qemu I add these:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>CONFIG_HYPERVISOR_GUEST=y\nCONFIG_PARAVIRT=y\nCONFIG_KVM_GUEST=y\nCONFIG_PVH=y\nCONFIG_SERIAL_EARLYCON=y\nCONFIG_SERIAL_8250=y\nCONFIG_SERIAL_8250_CONSOLE=y\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 419019514,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1706700452
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"582232\">Matt Gilbride</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Build.20error.20on.20rust.20next.20when.20using.20minimal.20.2Econfig/near/419019459\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>hm...<br>\n<code>make olddefconfig</code></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code>#\n#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">No</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">change</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span>\n#\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then, later, here is the first thing I'm blindly ignoring by accepting the default:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Link</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Time</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Optimization</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LTO</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">1.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">None</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LTO_NONE</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">2.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Clang</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Full</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LTO</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EXPERIMENTAL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LTO_CLANG_FULL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">NEW</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">3.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Clang</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ThinLTO</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EXPERIMENTAL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LTO_CLANG_THIN</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">NEW</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">choice</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>:\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I'm on a linux machine, x86_64, FWIW:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Operating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">System</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Debian</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GNU</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Linux</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rodete</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Kernel</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Linux</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">6.5.13</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"n\">rodete2</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">amd64</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Architecture</span>: <span class=\"nc\">x86</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">64</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><code>olddefconfig</code> should take care of these questions for you. But you need to pass all the stuff to make that you do when building, for instance <code>LLVM=1</code></p>",
        "id": 419019711,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1706700525
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>LTO _CLANG is not available when building with gcc, and when you did <code>olddefconfig</code> you used the default compiler, which is gcc. When you then build with llvm, the option appears as new without any setting.</p>",
        "id": 419020027,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1706700654
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>For the minimal config I have arrived at this: make allnoconfig and then merge in these:</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Do you use <code>scripts/kconfig/merge_config.sh</code> to do that? (forgive me, that's what googling says to do)</p>",
        "id": 419020203,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1706700726
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"582232\">Matt Gilbride</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Build.20error.20on.20rust.20next.20when.20using.20minimal.20.2Econfig/near/419020203\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>For the minimal config I have arrived at this: make allnoconfig and then merge in these:</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Do you use <code>scripts/kconfig/merge_config.sh</code> to do that? (forgive me, that's what googling says to do)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Answering my own question...this worked, thank you <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"498029\">@Andreas Hindborg</span> .  I'll leave the thought about adding this to the docs (something about <code>allnoconfig</code> + merge in your minimal set) to you all.   My understanding is this might encourage people to do the minimum and then not properly test real configs for real world devices.</p>",
        "id": 419021957,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1706701435
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"582232\">Matt Gilbride</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Build.20error.20on.20rust.20next.20when.20using.20minimal.20.2Econfig/near/419020203\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>For the minimal config I have arrived at this: make allnoconfig and then merge in these:</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Do you use <code>scripts/kconfig/merge_config.sh</code> to do that? (forgive me, that's what googling says to do)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I do. For configs that live inside the kernel tree at <code>/kernel/configs</code>, you can do something like <code>make rust.config</code>. I have quite a few config fragments and I like to keep them out of tree so they don't get lost when I move between branches and commits, and so they don't clutter my tree. Instead I have this script (<a href=\"https://github.com/casey/just\">justfile</a> fragment):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Makefile\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">config path=\"linux\" +FRAGMENTS=\"null\"</span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"c\">    #!/bin/bash</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nb\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-e\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nb\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-x\n<span class=\"w\">    </span>rm<span class=\"w\"> </span>-f<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>-build/.config\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">version</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"k\">$(</span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>/scripts/min-tool-version.sh<span class=\"w\"> </span>bindgen<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nb\">export</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">PATH</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"{{top}}/bindgen-</span><span class=\"nv\">$version</span><span class=\"s2\">/bin:</span><span class=\"nv\">$PATH</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>make<span class=\"w\"> </span>-j<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>nproc<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">O</span><span class=\"o\">={{</span>top<span class=\"o\">}}</span>/<span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>-build<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"m\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span>allnoconfig<span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>/scripts/kconfig/merge_config.sh<span class=\"w\"> </span>-m<span class=\"w\"> </span>-O<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>-build<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>-build/.config<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span>config/default.fragment<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"sb\">`</span><span class=\"nb\">echo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"{{FRAGMENTS}}\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>sed<span class=\"w\"> </span>-E<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s1\">'s#([^[:space:]]+)#config/\\1.fragment#g'</span><span class=\"sb\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>make<span class=\"w\"> </span>-j<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>nproc<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">O</span><span class=\"o\">={{</span>top<span class=\"o\">}}</span>/<span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>-build<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"m\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span>olddefconfig<span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>So I can create a new linux git worktree and go like <code>just config my_worktree kvm rust</code></p>",
        "id": 419022785,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1706701807
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I also have this one that I run first to set the right compiler and bindgen version:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Makefile\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">rustup path=\"linux\"</span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"c\">    #!/bin/bash</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">version</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"k\">$(</span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>/scripts/min-tool-version.sh<span class=\"w\"> </span>bindgen<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">rustc_version</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"k\">$(</span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>/scripts/min-tool-version.sh<span class=\"w\"> </span>rustc<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span>mkdir<span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>-build\n<span class=\"w\">    </span>rustup<span class=\"w\"> </span>override<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>--path<span class=\"o\">={{</span>path<span class=\"o\">}}</span>-build<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">$rustc_version</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span>cargo<span class=\"w\"> </span>install<span class=\"w\"> </span>bindgen-cli<span class=\"w\"> </span>--locked<span class=\"w\"> </span>--version<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"nv\">$version</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>--root<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span><span class=\"nb\">pwd</span><span class=\"k\">)</span>/bindgen-<span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"nv\">$version</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span>rustup<span class=\"w\"> </span>component<span class=\"w\"> </span>add<span class=\"w\"> </span>--toolchain<span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"nv\">$rustc_version</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>rust-src\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 419022890,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1706701855
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Bindgen is not an issue these days, but there was a period where I would move between bindgen versions and that always got me.</p>",
        "id": 419023027,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1706701915
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>So I can create a new linux git worktree and go like just config my_worktree kvm rust<br>\nI also have this one that I run first to set the right compiler and bindgen version:</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>These both look quite handy, thank you!</p>",
        "id": 419023629,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1706702136
    }
]